AOI Fiat

Source: vignettes/aoi_fiat.Rmd
aoi_fiat.Rmd

The AOI package provides a bridge between the spatial data stored in rnaturalearth and USAboundaries to provide consistent programmatic access to fiat (non-physical boundaries that exclusively depend on acts of human decision) boundaries.

Using the aoi_get query users can query country, USA state, and USA county data from a single interface. Examples of these queries can be seen below. In all examples the AOI function aoi_map is used to generate quick leaflet views of the requested AOI(s)

AOI by country

An AOI can be defined by a country name, abbreviation, or ISO code:

Single

Country data can be queried individually,

aoi_get(country = 'CR') %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

Multiple

As a set,

aoi_get(country = c('Brazil', 'PERU', "chile")) %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

AOI by USA state

An AOI in the United States,can be defined by state name or abbreviation.

Single

Again single states,

aoi_get(state = 'CA') %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = T)

Multiple states:

aoi_get(state = c("Oregon", "Washington", "CA")) %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

If you want the lower 48 USA state you can query state = 'conus'.

aoi_get(state = "conus") %>% aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

Region

aoi_get(state = "south") %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

Combined calls

Calls to country can be mixed with calls to state.

aoi_get(country = "Mexico", state = c("CA", "NM", "AZ", 'TX')) %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

AOI by county

If you want to get the boundaries of a state with the county features intact, simply call aoi_get and set county = 'all'

aoi_get(state = "AL", county = 'all') %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

Otherwise, single, and collections of counties can be queried:

Single

aoi_get(state = "CO", county = "El Paso") %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)

Multiple

aoi_get(state ="CA", county = c("Santa Barbara", "San Luis Obispo", "Ventura")) %>% aoi_map(returnMap = T)

Counties in different states

aoi_get(state =c("CA", "CO"), county = c("Santa Barbara", "El Paso")) %>% aoi_map(returnMap = T)
aoi_get(state ='northeast', county = 'all') %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = T)

Unioning

The union parameter automatically unions as features as a single geometry.

aoi_get(state = c('CA', 'OR', 'WA'), union = TRUE) %>% 
  aoi_map(returnMap = TRUE)
